[Student "S"]
{SOUTH's 2\D bid is a perfect example of NMF. 
It provides NORTH with the opportunity to show either a 4-card \H suit, 
OR 3-card \S support.

In this hand NORTH actually has both. When that happens, showing the \Hs is 
first priority.}

